The police in Bayelsa State on Monday raided a hideout of hard drugs suppliers in Akaba community, a suburb of Yenagoa, the state capital. Asimin Butswat, spokesperson for the police in the state, in a statement said operatives of Operation Puff adder stormed the hideout where criminals gather to smoke cocaine, Indian hemp before going out to commit their nefarious activities in Yenagoa.  He disclosed that no arrest had been made even though the place was set ablaze by the police.